      • getAddNode

        private GNode getAddNode(double latitude,
                         double longitude,
                         int low,
                         int high,
                         boolean allowAdd)
        !!! GNode object in ArrayList nodes are stored sorted to retrieve already existing points fast !!! This is only done in GGraphTile during setup of the graph.
        Parameters:
        latitude - latitude of the point to be stored
        longitude - longitude of the point to be stored
        low - nodes.get(low) is strict less (or low is -1)
        high - nodes.get(high) is strict greater than (or high is nodes.size() )
        allowAdd - if set, then add a new node, if there is none with these lat/lon values (false is used for pure search)
        Returns:
        GNode with latitude an longitude, either already existing point or newly created one
